      <c01 level="series">
        <did>
          <unittitle>Church Activities and Membership <unitdate type="inclusive" normal="1925/2008">1925-2008</unitdate></unittitle>
        </did>
        <scopecontent>
          <p>The second series, Church Activities and Membership, is arranged into four subseries. Membership includes new and active member lists from 1925 to 2008, records of baptisms, and obituaries and memorial resolutions. Bulletins and Church Publications includes copies of church bulletins from 1970 to 2007, along with assorted programs and newsletters for events and special services, and Sunday School minutes. Building Expansion, Historic Site Designation, and Church Anniversaries documents the growth of the church building, its designation as an historic site by the State of Michigan and the city of Battle Creek, and celebrations of the church's anniversaries. Histories of the Church and Church Activities includes histories of the church, its choirs and musical programs, pastors, and the Women's Missionary Committee, compiled by the church's historian, Frank R. Brown, and the church's Black Heritage Committee. The majority of the histories contain historical narratives, photographs of church members, events, and facilities, photocopies of documents, and clippings.</p>
        </scopecontent>
